-- Trianel Arranges $724 Million Financing for German Offshore Wind Farm
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2010-12-21T11:07:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/trianel-arranges-724-million-financing-for-german-offshore-wind-farm.html
Trianel GmbH said it arranged $724
million in financing for an offshore wind farm in the German
section of the North Sea, tapping 11 banks including Unicredit
SpA and Dexia AG for a loan.  The European Investment Bank, KfW Ipex-Bank and Rabobank
were also involved in financing the 200-megawatt project.  To contact the reporter on this story:
